premise_source_doc_sentence: He succeed his elder brother Abu ` l-Asakir Jaysh , who had been murdered by army chiefs .
Abu ` l-Asakir Jaysh ibn Khumarawayh  (  أبو العساكر جيش بن خمارويه born c. 882  )  was the third Emir of the Tulunids in Egypt , ruling briefly in 896 .
In Chinese Buddhism , the Mass that Maudgalyayana held to save his mother who had gone to the Hungry Ghost realm  (  one of the Six realms  )  is the foundation of ullambana  (  Ghost Festival  )  .

In April 2015 , Here Be Dragons produced Walking New York , a VR experience made in partnership with the New York Times which follows JR  (  artist  )  and his making of a 150-foot-tall portrait of a recent immigrant to NYC that was wheat pasted across the Flatiron Building Pedestrian Plaza for less than 24 hours .
Here Be Dragons continued its partnership with the United Nations to create the VR experience Waves of Grace in October 2015 .
